				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't know much about showeq so I can't speak for or of it. I am not a computer programer nor am I familar with unix or linux. However I do play both  a beastlord and mage and have played a necro. 
<br />

<br />
 I can personally attest that beastlord pets are not beastlords. I realise it has been suggested they were in the past however it has been my experience that those who writes press releases often don't actually play the game so actually know very little about what they are talking about. Beastlord warders are fully capable of using weapons that beastlords can not use and do so with no loss of combat performance. 
<br />
 Mage pets are also capable of weilding all weapons. Now I do fully agree that post 50 the mage pets are coded to reflect certain class abilities however the pre 50 pets are simply NPC's each with a unique inherit spell/s they cast as well as a variable in their evasion/absorbtion ac qualities as well as their hp and attack levels. I believe people see those variables as indicators for actual class's however I believe that those analogies are approximations not literal statements. To suggest that the earth pet is like a warrior for it possesses alot of damage absorbition ac but actually does the least damage while a fire pet is like a caster due to it's higher damage output due to the ds but less hp and less ac.<br />_________________<br />Member of the guild Wings of Valor on the E-marr server.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
